{"title_page": "Fasa", "text_new": "{{other uses}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name =Fasa\n|native_name = \u0641\u064e\u0633\u0627\n|settlement_type        = City\n|image_skyline = \u06af\u0646\u0628\u062f \u0648 \u06af\u0644\u062f\u0633\u062a\u0647 \u0632\u06cc\u0628\u0627\u06cc \u0622\u0633\u062a\u0627\u0646 \u0634\u0627\u0647\u0632\u0627\u062f\u0647 \u0642\u0627\u0633\u0645 \u0641\u0633\u0627.jpg\n|imagesize = \n|image_caption = \n|pushpin_map            =Iran\n|mapsize                =150px\n|subdivision_type       = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n|subdivision_name = {{flag|Iran}}\n|subdivision_type1 =[[Provinces of Iran|Province]]\n|subdivision_name1 =[[Fars Province|Fars]]\n|subdivision_type2 =[[Counties of Iran|County]]\n|subdivision_name2 =[[Fasa County|Fasa]]\n|subdivision_type3 =[[Bakhsh]]\n|subdivision_name3 =[[Central District (Fasa County)|Central]]\n|leader_title           = \n|leader_name            = \n|established_title      =\n|established_date       = \n|area_total_km2         = 25.5\n| area_rank = 3rd\n|area_footnotes         = \n|population_as_of       = 2016 Census\n|population_urban      = 110,825 <ref>https://www.amar.org.ir/english</ref>\n|population_density_km2   =4,346\n| population_blank1_title         = Population Rank\n| population_blank1               = 4th\n|timezone               = [[Iran Standard Time|IRST]]\n|utc_offset             = +3:30\n|timezone_DST           = [[Iran Daylight Time|IRDT]]\n|utc_offset_DST         = +4:30\n|coordinates            = {{coord|28|56|18|N|53|38|54|E|region:IR|display=inline,title}}\n|elevation_m              = 1150\n|website                  = {{URL|shfasa.ir/}}\n|area_code =  \n|footnotes              =\n}}\n'''Fasa''' ({{lang-fa|\u0641\u0633\u0627}}, also [[Romanize]]d as '''Fassa''')<ref>{{GEOnet3|-3062808}}</ref> is a city and capital of [[Fasa County]], [[Fars Province]], [[Iran]]. At the 2016 census, its population was 110,825, in 33,379 families. Fasa is the fourth most populous city of the province.<ref>{{IranCensus2016|07}}</ref> The city dates back to the [[Achaemenid]] period.<ref name=\"from pasa\"/>\n\nFasa's economy is based on agriculture and Pastoralism. [[Jahrom]], [[Darab]], [[Sarvestan]], [[Kherameh]] and [[Estahban]] are neighbours of Fasa. This city is located on the road from [[Shiraz]] to [[Kerman]], This has made Fasa a strategic and important city.\n\n== Name==\n[[File:Fasa - panoramio.jpg|250px|thumb|right|northern entrance of Fasa]]\nIn the inscriptions of [[Persepolis]], Fasa is mentioned as \"Pashiya\" or \"Bashiya\". Based on the contents of Tablet No. 53 of [[Persepolis Administrative Archives]], George Glenn Cameron considers the location of the city of \"Pashiya\" or \"Bashiya\" to correspond to the current location of the city of Fasa. The word \"Bashiya\" is actually the [[Elamite]] form of the word Pasa. Due to the lack of the letter \"P\" in Arabic, the word was pronounced \"Basa\" and sometimes \"Fasa\" after the [[Muslim conquest of Persia]] and cultural exchanges. Fasa literally means \"residence and camp\". Researchers have also considered the meaning of the word Fasa \"the city of the [[Persians]]\".<ref name=\"from pasa\"/><ref name=\"university\">{{cite web | url=http://www.fasau.ac.ir/%D8%AF%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%B4%DA%AF%D8%A7%D9%87-%D9%81%D8%B3%D8%A7/%D8%A7%D8%B7%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%A7%D8%AA/about-fasa | title=About Fasa | publisher=University of Fasa | accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== History==\nFasa is one of the historical cities of Iran. The city dates back to the [[Achaemenid]] period, when the city's name was \"Pasa\" or \"Pashiya\". In the [[Sassanid]] period, the remains of the old city, the fortress and the Sassanid fire temple, and also the presence of the Fasaei people in the political and cultural affairs of that time, show that Fasa had a special position and prosperity during this period. Fasa was [[Muslim conquest of Persia|conquered by the Muslims]] in 638 after a fierce battle. Fasa was the second most important city of [[Darabgerd]] province in the tenth century. Urban Foundations of Fasa (Grand Mosque, Bazaar, Bath, etc.) was established during the [[Safavid]] period and expanded during the [[Afsharid]]s. Epidemics, famines, political games, insecurity and looting were among the most important factors in the destruction and decline of Fasa's prosperity during the [[Qajar]] period.<ref name=\"from pasa\"/>\n\n== Climate ==\nFasa has a [[hot semi-arid climate]] ([[K\u00f6ppen climate classification]]: ''BSh''). Its average rainfall is about {{convert|290|mm|in}} per year.\n{{Weather box\n|location=Fasa\n|width=auto\n|metric first = Y\n|single line = Y\n|Jan record high C =20\n|Feb record high C =23\n|Mar record high C =27\n|Apr record high C =34\n|May record high C =37\n|Jun record high C =41\n|Jul record high C =42\n|Aug record high C =40\n|Sep record high C =39\n|Oct record high C =33\n|Nov record high C =30\n|Dec record high C =24\n|year record high C =42\n\n|Jan high C =9\n|Feb high C =13\n|Mar high C =17\n|Apr high C =23\n|May high C =29\n|Jun high C =34\n|Jul high C =36\n|Aug high C =36\n|Sep high C =32\n|Oct high C =26\n|Nov high C =19\n|Dec high C =13\n|year high C = 36\n\n|Jan mean C = 8\n|Feb mean C = 9\n|Mar mean C = 12\n|Apr mean C = 16\n|May mean C = 22\n|Jun mean C = 28\n|Jul mean C = 31\n|Aug mean C = 30\n|Sep mean C = 27\n|Oct mean C = 22\n|Nov mean C = 16\n|Dec mean C = 10\n|year mean C = 18\n\n|Jan low C =1\n|Feb low C =3\n|Mar low C =7\n|Apr low C =12\n|May low C =17\n|Jun low C =22\n|Jul low C =24\n|Aug low C =23\n|Sep low C =19\n|Oct low C =13\n|Nov low C =7\n|Dec low C =4\n|year low C =24\n\n|Jan record low C =-12\n|Feb record low C =-2\n|Mar record low C =-3\n|Apr record low C =-2\n|May record low C =7\n|Jun record low C =11\n|Jul record low C =16\n|Aug record low C =13\n|Sep record low C =7\n|Oct record low C =3\n|Nov record low C =-5\n|Dec record low C =-5\n|year record low C =\n\n|precipitation colour = green\n|Jan precipitation mm = 68\n|Feb precipitation mm = 66\n|Mar precipitation mm = 49\n|Apr precipitation mm = 33\n|May precipitation mm = 7\n|Jun precipitation mm = 0\n|Jul precipitation mm = 0\n|Aug precipitation mm = 2\n|Sep precipitation mm = 0\n|Oct precipitation mm = 0\n|Nov precipitation mm = 10\n|Dec precipitation mm = 55\n|year precipitation mm = 292\n|source=www.myforecast.com<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.myforecast.com/bin/climate.m?city=66228&metric=true= | title=Fasa climate | publisher=www.myforecast.com | accessdate=25 July 2010}}</ref>, Fars province Meteorological Organization<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.farsmet.ir/DM/Files/files/fasa.pdf |title=Fasa |last= |first= |date= |website=Fars province Meteorological Organization |publisher= |access-date=2020-04-08 |quote=}}</ref>\n|accessdate=\n}}\n\n== Demographics ==\nAt the 2016 census, its population was 110,825, in 33,379 families.<ref>{{IranCensus2016|07}}</ref> people of Fasa speak [[Persian language]]. There is also a significant [[Khamseh Arabs|Khamseh Arab]] minority in Fasa. Almost all of the people are [[Shia]] [[Muslim]]s.<ref name=\"from pasa\">{{cite book | title=From Pasa to Pasa | publisher=Fanoos Andisheh | author=Rezazadeh, Jalil | year=2009 | isbn=9786009085521}}</ref>\n\n{{Historical populations|1976|31489|1986|64771|1991|74478|1996|81706|2006|92020|2011|104809|2016|110825|align=center}}\n\n== Economy ==\n[[File:\u0646\u0627\u0646 \u0641\u0633\u0627\u06cc\u06cc.jpg|thumb|220px|The \"Fasaei bread\"]]\nFasa is thriving in terms of agriculture. Fasa is known as the city of [[wheat]]. Due to the favorable climate, [[Arecaceae|palms]], [[walnut]] trees, and [[citrus]] such as [[oranges]], [[tangerines]], [[pomegranates]], [[pistachios]], [[almonds]], and [[walnuts]] are common in this city. [[Cotton]] cultivation has also flourished in Fasa.<ref name=\"agriculture\">{{cite web | url=http://portal.farstr.ir/portal/show.aspx?page=17178 | title=Fasa introduction | publisher=Fars Province Rural Cooperative Organization | accessdate=8 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[Pastoralism]] is the second base of Fasa's economy. A variety of livestock and dairy products, wool, leather, meat, are the products of the city.\n\nThere is also an under construction petrochemical project in the city. The construction stated in 2012 and after the complete operation, It will produce Low density polyethylenes.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.shiraznovinnews.ir/news-details/9742-%D8%BA%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1-10%D8%B3%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%87-%D8%B1%D9%88%DB%8C-%D9%BE%D8%B1%D9%88%D9%86%D8%AF%D9%87-%D9%BE%D8%AA%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B4%DB%8C%D9%85%DB%8C-%D9%81%D8%B3%D8%A7 | title=Fasa petrochemical project | publisher=Shiraz Novin News | accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Souvenirs ===\nThe \"Fasaei bread\" ({{lang-fa|\u0646\u0627\u0646 \u0641\u0633\u0627\u06cc\u06cc}}) is the most significant and the main souvenir of Fasa city. [[Kilim]], [[Gabbeh]], [[Jajim]], [[Lemon]], [[Orange (fruit)|Orange]], [[Tangerine]], [[Pomegranate]], [[Walnut]], [[Pistachio]] and handicrafts are other souvenirs of this city.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.iribnews.ir/fa/news/1573198/%D9%86%D8%A7%D9%86-%D9%81%D8%B3%D8%A7%DB%8C%DB%8C-%D8%B3%D9%88%D8%BA%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D8%B4%DB%8C%D8%B1%DB%8C%D9%86-%D9%81%D8%B3%D8%A7 | title=Fasaei bread, the sweet souvenirs of Fasa | publisher=IRIB News | accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Education==\n[[File:Fasa islamic azad university.jpg|thumb|240px|Islamic Azad University of Fasa]]\n===Colleges and universities===\n* [http://www.fasau.ac.ir/ Fasa University] \n* [http://www.fums.ac.ir/ Fasa University of Medical Sciences]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20080914160215/http://reg.pnu.ac.ir./ Fasa Payam Noor University]\n* [http://www.iaufasa.ac.ir/ Islamic Azad University of Fasa]\n* [[Technical and Vocational University|Technical and Agricultural college of Fasa]]\n\n==Health and Cure==\nFasa has two hospitals in operation and one hospital under construction.\n*Valie Asr Hospital\n*Dr. Shariati Hospital\n*Emam Hossein Hospital (under construction)<ref name=\"fums\">{{cite web | url=http://www.fums.ac.ir/ | title=Fasa university of medical sciences | accessdate=8 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Clinics ===\n*Valie Asr Clinic\n*Hamzeh Clinic\n*Yasaei Clinic<ref name=\"fums\"/>\n\n==Transport==\n===Roads===\nShiraz-Fasa highway, The highway which connects Fasa to Shiraz is in operation. Fasa-Darab and Fasa-Estahban-Neyriz highway projects are also under construction.<ref name=\"highway\">{{cite web | url=https://www.yjc.ir/fa/news/7107999/%D8%A8%D9%87%D8%B1%D9%87-%D8%A8%D8%B1%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%B1%DB%8C-%D8%A7%D8%B2-%DB%B3%DB%B0-%DA%A9%DB%8C%D9%84%D9%88%D9%85%D8%AA%D8%B1-%D8%A8%D8%B2%D8%B1%DA%AF%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%87-%D9%81%D8%B3%D8%A7-%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%A8-%D8%AA%D8%A7-%D9%BE%D8%A7%DB%8C%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%85%D8%B3%D8%A7%D9%84 | title=Exploitation of 30 km of Fasa Darab highway by the end of this year | publisher=YJC | accessdate=8 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Railway===\nCurrently, the Shiraz-Golgohar railway is passing through Fasa with the aim of connecting Shiraz to the Golgohar mines and [[Kerman province]]. The length of this route is {{convert|346|km|mi}}, which is under construction in 4 phases and connects Shiraz to Golgohar through [[Sarvestan]], Fasa, [[Estahban]] and [[Neyriz]].<ref name=\"railway\">{{cite web | url=https://shiraz1400.ir/?p=40467 | title=Allocation of 35 billion tomans to Shiraz-Golgohar railway | publisher=Shiraz 1400 | accessdate=8 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Airport===\n[[Fasa Airport]] is an airport near Fasa. The airport is currently inactive, but studies of the airport's development plan, improving and increasing the length of the runway with the aim of resuming commercial flights are beeing done. The airport has a {{convert|1982|m|ft}} runway.<ref name=\"airport\">{{cite web | url=https://fasa.airport.ir/ | title=Fasa Airport | publisher=Iran Airports Company | accessdate=8 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Attractions and Monuments ==\n[[File:\u0636\u0631\u06cc\u062d \u0645\u0646\u0648\u0631 \u0622\u0633\u062a\u0627\u0646 \u0634\u0627\u0647\u0632\u0627\u062f\u0647 \u0642\u0627\u0633\u0645 \u0648 \u0634\u0627\u0647\u0632\u0627\u062f\u0647 \u0627\u0628\u0631\u0627\u0647\u06cc\u0645 \u0639\u0644\u06cc\u0647\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u0633\u0644\u0627\u0645.jpg|thumb|230px|Imamzadeh Qasem]]\n* Tale Zahak\n* Tale Nalaki\n* Imamzadeh Hasan\n* Imamzadeh Qasem\n* Imamzadeh Ismael\n* Mianjangal Jungle\n* Kharmankooh mountain\n* Sassanid fire temple\n* The Naghare-khane building<ref>{{cite web | url=http://en.fums.ac.ir/about-us/about-fasa | title=About Fasa | publisher=Fasa University of Medical Sciences (FUMS) | accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikivoyage}}\n{{Commons category}}\n*[http://shfasa.ir/ municipality of Fasa]\n\n{{Fars Province}}\n{{Fasa County}}\n\n{{Portal|Iran}}\n\n[[Category:Fasa| ]]\n[[Category:Populated places in Fasa County]]\n[[Category:Cities in Fars Province]]\n\n\n{{Fasa-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{other uses}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name =Fasa\n|native_name = \u0641\u064e\u0633\u0627\n|settlement_type        = City\n|image_skyline = \u06af\u0646\u0628\u062f \u0648 \u06af\u0644\u062f\u0633\u062a\u0647 \u0632\u06cc\u0628\u0627\u06cc \u0622\u0633\u062a\u0627\u0646 \u0634\u0627\u0647\u0632\u0627\u062f\u0647 \u0642\u0627\u0633\u0645 \u0641\u0633\u0627.jpg\n|imagesize = \n|image_caption = \n|pushpin_map            =Iran\n|mapsize                =150px\n|subdivision_type       = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n|subdivision_name = {{flag|Iran}}\n|subdivision_type1 =[[Provinces of Iran|Province]]\n|subdivision_name1 =[[Fars Province|Fars]]\n|subdivision_type2 =[[Counties of Iran|County]]\n|subdivision_name2 =[[Fasa County|Fasa]]\n|subdivision_type3 =[[Bakhsh]]\n|subdivision_name3 =[[Central District (Fasa County)|Central]]\n|leader_title           = \n|leader_name            = \n|established_title      =\n|established_date    