" | [[Russell County, Alabama|Russell]]\n|26\n|0\n|52,947\n|49\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" | [[Shelby County, Alabama|Shelby]]\n|229\n|5\n|195,085\n|117\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" | [[St. Clair County, Alabama|St. Clair]]\n|43\n|0\n|83,593\n|51\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" | [[Sumter County, Alabama|Sumter]]\n|21\n|0\n|13,763\n|153\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" | [[Talladega County, Alabama|Talladega]]\n|38\n|1\n|82,291\n|46\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" | [[Tallapoosa County, Alabama|Tallapoosa]]\n|100\n|5\n|41,616\n|240\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" | [[Tuscaloosa County, Alabama|Tuscaloosa]]\n|120\n|0\n|194,656\n|62\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" | [[Walker County, Alabama|Walker]]\n|83\n|0\n|67,023\n|124\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" | [[Washington County, Alabama|Washington]]\n|12\n|1\n|17,581\n|68\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" | [[Wilcox County, Alabama|Wilcox]]\n|30\n|0\n|11,670\n|257\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\" | [[Winston County, Alabama|Winston]]\n|4\n|0\n|24,484\n|16\n|- class=\"sortbottom\"\n! style=\"text-align:right;\" |Total\n! style=\"text-align:right;\" |3,734\n|'''99'''\n|4,903,185\n|76\n|}\n\n===Demographics===\n{{Graph:Chart\n | width=100\n | height=100\n | type=pie\n | legend=Case percentages by race\n | x=White (46.8%),Black/African-American (36.7%),Pending (13.6%),Other/Multi-racial (1.9%),Asian (1%)\n | y1=46.8,36.7,13.6,1.9,1\n}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n{{2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States}}\n{{Portal bar|Coronavirus disease 2019|Medicine|Pandemic|United States|Viruses}}\n\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States by state|Alabama]]\n[[Category:2020 in Alabama|coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:Disasters in Alabama]]\n[[Category:Health in Alabama]]\n[[Category:March 2020 events in the United States|coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:April 2020 events in the United States|coronavirus pandemic]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Details of ongoing viral pandemic in Alabama, United States}}\n{{Current disaster|event=pandemic|date=March 2020}}\n{{use mdy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Alabama\n| map1            = \n| legend1         = \n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Alabama]], U.S.\n| first_case      = [[Montgomery County, Alabama|Montgomery County]]\n| arrival_date    = March 13, 2020\n| confirmed_cases = 3,809<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://alabamapublichealth.gov/infectiousdiseases/2019-coronavirus.html|title=Alabama Department of Public Health (ADPH)}}</ref>\n| deaths          = 73\n| website         = [https://www.alabamapublichealth.gov/infectiousdiseases/2019-coronavirus.html Alabama Department of Public Health]\n| hospitalized_cases = 493\n}}\n\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] was confirmed to have reached the U.S. state of [[Alabama]] in March 2020. As of April 13, 2020, the Alabama Department of Public Health reported 3,809 cases of COVID-19 and 73 deaths.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.alabamapublichealth.gov/infectiousdiseases/2019-coronavirus.html|title=Coronavirus Disease 2019 (COVID-19) {{!}} Alabama Department of Public Health (ADPH)|website=Alabama Department of Public Health|access-date=April 14, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.wsfa.com/2020/03/17/adph-update-public-covid-am/|title=Alabama coronavirus cases climb to 39; Closures ordered in some counties|author=WSFA Staff|website=WSFA|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref>\n\n== Timeline ==\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/United States/Alabama medical cases chart}}\n\n{{Bar chart\n| float       = right\n| title         = New Cases Reported Per Day in Alabama\n| caption       = '''Source''':  data in the chart, \"COVID-19 <br/> \ncases in Alabama, United States,\" shown <br/>\nabove.\n| label_type    = Date\n| data_type     = New Cas